ns305:ArrayDesign.description: The cDNA microarray chips contained 7651 total features and were manufactured at the National Cancer Institute microarray facility. The cDNAclones used are identified by their Integrated Molecular Analysis of Genomes and their Expression Consortium (I.M.A.G.E.) clone number.

ns315:ArrayDesign.name: GP_KKWONG UniGem10K
ns315:ArrayDesign.description: The cDNA microarrays were fabricated with the Easy-to-Spot Human UniGene 1 PCR products (Incyte Genomics, Palo Alto, CA) that consist of a total of 9,216 unique elements. The PCR products were printed in duplicate along with three Arabidopsis cDNA for detecting spike-in controls using an OmniGrid Accent Arrayer (GeneMachines, San Carlos, CA) equipped with 24 SMP3 pins (TeleChem International, Sunnyvale, CA). All PCR products were resequenced before printing to validate their annotation.

ns330:ArrayDesign.name: Mu11KsubB
ns330:ArrayDesign.description: Affymetrix Mu11k GeneChips, interrogating 13,104 genes and ESTs on two different arrays, were processed according to the manufacturer’s recommendations. Approximately 20 pairs of oligonucleotides (probe pairs) represent every gene or EST in a probe set, with one sequence being complementary to the target sequence and the other having a 1-bp mismatch in a central position. This serves as an internal control for hybridization specificity. This is the array B within the set

ns335:ArrayDesign.name: Mu11KsubA
ns335:ArrayDesign.description: Affymetrix Mu11k GeneChips contains 13,104 genes and ESTs on two different arrays. Approximately 20 pairs of oligonucleotides (probe pairs) represent every gene or EST in a probe set, with one sequence being complementary to the target sequence and the other having a 1-bp mismatch in a central position. This serves as an internal control for hybridization specificity. This is the A array from a set of 2 and it has a total of 6585 probe sets.

ns340:ArrayDesign.name: HumArray 1.14
ns340:ArrayDesign.description: This array was designed for copy-number assessments across the human genome. We printed 2,460 BAC and P1 clones in triplicate (approx. 7,500 elements) in a 12mm X 12mm square. Each clone contains at least one STS, allowing linkage to the genome sequence. Cytogenetic mapping indicated that 2,298 of the arrayed clones are single copy; this array thus provides average resolution of approximately 1.4 Mb across the genome.
